v1.0.0

NAME
    PCIUTILS::LSPCI - perl postprocess `lspci` output

SYNOPSIS
        use PCIUTILS::LSPCI;

        $obj = PCIUTILS::LSPCI->new;
        $lspci = $obj->get_lspci;

        ## Equivalent to `lspci -D -n`
        for $record (@$lspci) {
            $s = $record->{Slot};
            $v = $record->{Vendor};
            $d = $record->{Device};
            $c = $record->{Class};
            $r = $record->{Rev};
            print "$s $c: $v:$d";
            print " (rev $r)" if defined $r;
            print "\n";
        }

DESCRIPTION
    Provide perl interface to PCI information as returned by lspci(1).

  Methods
    new Constructor. Build lspci internal hash.

    get_lspci
        Parsed output from "lspci", returned as arrayref:

        Note: the lspci hash is built at contruction time, see "Internals".

  Internals
    _lspci
        Run "lspci -D -n -vmm", parse, return arrayref.

SEE ALSO
    lspci(1)

